               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="fr">French</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> Charter dated <origDate when="1375">5 April, 1375</origDate>, reciting that 
                  <persName>sir <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Atoun</surname>
                        </persName> the father, 
                  in the presence of the <persName>sire de <surname>Percy</surname>
                        </persName>, challenged 
                  <persName>sir <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Boneton</surname>
                        </persName> on account of 
                  the arms he bore, namely, Or, on a cross sable five bullocks' heads argent, which matter after long
                  controversy, was submitted to the judgement of the sire de Percy, who after deliberation
                  adjudged the arms to belong to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Aton</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                  who thereupon grants the same to <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Boneton</surname>
                        </persName>
                  and his heirs for ever. [Defaced.]</p>
                  </msItem>
